	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />NES may not be "analog" per se, but it's still "virtual analog", meaning that it has the same capability as an analog synth. Pulse-width modulated oscillators, integrators (which turn a square into a triangle), and sample-and-hold noise generators are common analog circuits.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
